I have noticed that if a constant has sub items (in JS) that if you call of use them like
`const data = {
    "name":"Test"
};
console.log(data.name);
console.log(data);`

And look at the calling data (the one in the console log) in the developer tools then it has class "span.variable.other.object.js" but the declaration has "span.constant.other.js", the log of just the data also is "span.constant.other.js"

I believe that this is an error

Opening a 250KB file with 3992 lines of PHP code lets Atom really slow. The whole interface freezes and take about 1 minute to unfreeze.

Steps to reproduce
1 - Open Atom
2 - Add Project Folder
3 - Open the file
4 - Scroll to the end of file and hit enter (sometimes it's a BIT faster, but always stucking for a while)

The issue can be reproduced if you just copy the bellow code until it passes 3900 lines more or less, of course with complex files it get worse:

